THIRD-PARTY SOFTWARE

This product does not bundle or redistribute third-party source code. At
runtime it expects the user to install and run the following independent
components on their own machine. None of these are included in this
repository; they are installed by the user (or, optionally, by the C2G
Setup Wizard, which downloads them directly from their respective vendors).

  • Ollama — https://ollama.com — MIT License
    Local model runtime. Installed by the user via Homebrew (`brew install
    ollama`) or the Ollama macOS installer.

  • IBM Granite 4.1 — https://huggingface.co/ibm-granite — Apache 2.0 License
    Local language model. Pulled by the user via `ollama pull granite4.1:8b`
    (or :30b for the larger tier).

  • Homebrew (optional) — https://brew.sh — BSD-2-Clause License
    Package manager. Only invoked by the Setup Wizard if the user opts to
    install Ollama via Homebrew rather than the direct macOS installer.

  • Claude Desktop / Cowork / Claude Code — https://claude.com
    Anthropic-published clients that consume the ollama-delegate skill.
    Not redistributed by this project. Cloud2GroundAI does NOT call
    the Anthropic API directly; integration is entirely via the user's
    own Claude installation reading the skill from
    ~/.claude/skills/ollama-delegate/.

