DATA / PRIVACY DISCLOSURE

Cloud2GroundAI makes one outbound network connection by default, and it
carries no user content:

  • The bundled skill update channel defaults to "Stable," which fetches a
    JSON manifest from a Carlano-published HTTPS endpoint roughly once per
    24 hours to check for a newer skill version. No prompts, code, file
    contents, or other user content are sent. Set the channel to "Disabled"
    in Settings → Updates to turn this off entirely.

  • Anonymous usage telemetry and feedback/crash uploads are off by default
    and individually toggleable in the Privacy tab of the Settings panel.

User prompts, model responses, file contents, and conversation history
never leave the user's machine by default. See docs/faq.md for the full
data-handling description.
